This paper discusses a new algorithm for constructing scalable concurrent data structures, specifically a stack. The paper focuses on the synchronization paradigms of software combining and elimination, which are commonly used in concurrent data structure design. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents empirical evaluations, which could also fall under cs.PF (Performance).
